'''Jonathan Daniel Hamm''' (born March 10, 1971) is an American actor. He is best known for his role as [[Don Draper]] in the period drama series ''[[Mad Men]]'' (2007–2015),<ref name="tvg">{{cite web |title=Jon Hamm |url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jon-hamm/bio/190220/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906064826/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jon-hamm/bio/190220/ |archive-date=September 6, 2015 |publisher=[[TVGuide.com]]}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> for which he won [[List of awards and nominations received by Jon Hamm|numerous accolades]], including a [[Primetime Emmy Award]] and two [[Golden Globe Awards]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web|last=Costello|first=Quinn|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/general-news/golden-globes-jon-hamm-wins-853999/|title=Golden Globes: Jon Hamm Wins Best Actor in a TV Series, Drama|website=The Hollywood Reporter|date=January 10, 2016|access-date=May 4, 2021|archive-date=May 23, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523234621/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/general-news/golden-globes-jon-hamm-wins-853999/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Berkshire|first1=Geoff|last2=Friedlander|first2=Whitney|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/awards/emmy-awards-2015-jon-hamm-mad-men-1201597175/|title='Mad Men's' Jon Hamm on Finally Winning the Emmy|website=Variety|date=September 21, 2015|access-date=May 4, 2021|archive-date=May 23, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523234623/https://variety.com/2015/tv/awards/emmy-awards-2015-jon-hamm-mad-men-1201597175/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="emmys">{{Cite web |url=https://www.emmys.com/bios/jon-hamm |title=Jon Hamm – Emmy Awards, Nominations and Wins |website=Emmys.com |access-date=May 4, 2021 |archive-date=April 16, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416235223/https://www.emmys.com/bios/jon-hamm |url-status=live }}</ref>

Hamm also acted in lead roles in the films ''[[Stolen (2009 American film)|Stolen]]'' (2010), ''[[Million Dollar Arm]]'' (2014), ''[[Keeping Up with the Joneses (film)|Keeping Up with the Joneses]]'' (2016), ''[[Beirut (film)|Beirut]]'' (2018), and ''[[Confess, Fletch]]'' (2022), as well as his supporting roles in ''[[The Town (2010 film)|The Town]]'' (2010), ''[[Sucker Punch (2011 film)|Sucker Punch]]'' (2011), ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]'' (2011), ''[[Baby Driver]]'' (2017), ''[[Tag (2018 film)|Tag]]'' (2018), ''[[Bad Times at the El Royale]]'' (2018), ''[[The Report (2019 film)|The Report]]'' (2019), ''[[Richard Jewell (film)|Richard Jewell]]'' (2019), ''[[No Sudden Move]]'' (2021), and ''[[Top Gun: Maverick]]'' (2022).<ref name=":5">{{Cite web|date=September 6, 2015|title=Jon Hamm Credits {{!}} TVGuide.com|url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jon-hamm/credits/190220/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906071959/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jon-hamm/credits/190220/|url-status=dead|archive-date=September 6, 2015|access-date=July 25, 2021}}</ref> He also provided voice acting roles in the animated films ''[[Shrek Forever After]]'' (2010), ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]'' (2015), and ''[[Transformers One]]'' (2024).<ref name=":5" />

